  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening resilience capacities of pastoral communities in Moyale Sub-County</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">-To meet the immediate needs of the most vulnerable women and men affected by drought, while supporting them, their families and communities to recover and rebuild long-term resilience to future droughts.

 Improve Household food security by contributing to household income through unconditional  cash transfers
 Improve the household capacity to adapt to shocks by providing support in Management of livelihood resources and assets 
 Improve the living conditions and dignity of disaster-affected populations through the provision of essential basic services, including WASH, nutrition and food assistance
 Improve coping capacities and enhance access to livelihoods, early recovery and resilience by addressing the underlying causes of vulnerability through provision of conditional grants to community organised groups</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improve access to safe and adequate water to drought affected populations and will ensure that households receive enhanced hygiene promotion to prevent water-borne disease.
Project activities:
Outputs
Community water sources rehabilitated and constructed with an emphasis on sustainability.	
Activities
&#x2022;	Rehabilitation of water facilities (boreholes, pipe schemes, shallow wells).
&#x2022;	Supply of fast moving spare parts for servicing water supply equipment.
&#x2022;	Connecting health institutions and schools to water supplies
&#x2022;	Capacity building of Water Management Committees 
Objective 2: Ensure drought emergency affected communities receive enhanced hygiene promotion and adequate measures are developed to prevent and control cholera and other water-borne diseases.
Output
Emergency drought affected communities are practicing safe hygiene meeting WHO and sphere standards.
Activities
-Hygiene Promotion at households level (including promotion of hand-washing with soap)</narrative>
  </description>
